Dow up nearly 300 points on gains in Pfizer, Apple Inc. shares

The Dow Jones Industrial Average is rallying Monday morning with shares of Pfizer and Apple Inc. delivering the strongest returns for the blue-chip average. Shares of Pfizer PFE, -0.20% and Apple Inc. AAPL, -5.67% are contributing to the blue-chip gauge's intraday rally, as the Dow DJIA, -1.13% was most recently trading 295 points (1.1%) higher. Pfizer's shares have risen $1.58, or 4.7%, while those of Apple Inc. are up $14.01, or 3.6%, combining for an approximately 107-point bump for the Dow. Also contributing significantly to the gain are UnitedHealth UNH, 0.41%, Johnson & Johnson JNJ, -0.68%, and Home Depot HD, -1.31%. A $1 move in any of the Dow's 30 components equates to a 6.86-point swing.

